<quantity box="[284,369,632,658]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1025,589,917]" box="[151,421,675,701]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Forewing: dark brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1025,589,917]" box="[151,1025,718,744]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Transverse lines: black; terminal line marked by black dots between veins.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1025,589,917]" box="[151,886,762,788]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Reniform: distinct, whitish grey, very small, outlined by black.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1025,589,917]" box="[151,617,805,831]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Fringes: coloured like subterminal area.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1025,589,917]" box="[151,984,848,874]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Hindwing: unicolorous dark brown with an indistinct black discal spot.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1025,589,917]" box="[151,574,891,917]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Underside: unicolorous dark brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,977,1908]" box="[151,327,977,1003]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Male genitalia.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,977,1908]" box="[151,364,1020,1046]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Tegumen: narrow.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,977,1908]" box="[151,419,1063,1089]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Vinculum: short, stout.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,977,1908]" box="[151,441,1106,1132]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Saccus: U-shaped, short.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,977,1908]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Fultura superior: U-shaped with long, narrow arms, fused with upper middle part of tegumen and ventrally broadly with juxta-anellus on dorsal left side; a finger-like, apically blunt, ventrally directed process arises medially by fusion with juxta-anellus.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,977,1908]" box="[151,444,1279,1305]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Valve: shorter than wide.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,977,1908]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Ampulla: almost symmetrical, very long, bent subbasally, almost equally broad; densely setose with long hairlike setae bent inwards.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,977,1908]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2007" box="[151,230,1408,1434]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Pollex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pollex</taxonomicName>
: almost symmetrical, prominent, shorter than ampulla, basally broadest; subapically densely setose with long, hair-like setae bent inwards.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,977,1908]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Digitus: almost symmetrical, long, tapered, curved, directed slightly ventrally, apically pointed; right digitus slightly longer.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,977,1908]" box="[151,1196,1580,1606]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Juxta-anellus plate: large, higher than wide, hole for phallus positioned ventrally in plate.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,977,1908]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Phallus: relatively short, straight, slightly tapered towards apex; broadest by ductus ejaculatorius; coecum short and broad.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,977,1908]" box="[151,699,1710,1736]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Vesica: with a small, curved, pointed cornutus.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,977,1908]" box="[151,413,1753,1779]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="62.[151,1436,977,1908]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fibiger" authorityYear="2007" box="[151,352,1796,1821]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Pollex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schintlmeisteri">
<emphasis box="[151,352,1796,1821]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">P. schintlmeisteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other species by the almost symmetrical digitus, ampulla, and pollex, the short, finger-like, bent process from fultura superior, close to juxta-anellus, and the straight phallus, armed with a small, curved cornutus.
</paragraph>
